'''Mathis Rayan Cherki''' (born 17 August 2003) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for {{English football updater|ManchesC}} club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and the [[France national football team|France national team]].

== Early life ==
Rayan Cherki was born on 17 August 2003 in [[Lyon]], France and is of [[Algerians in France|Algerian]] and [[Italians in France|Italian]] descent. His father is half Algerian and half Italian, and his mother is Algerian from [[Biskra]].<ref name="Soccerway" /><ref>{{Cite web |last=Rahmani |first=Écrit par Mohamed |date=25 January 2025 |title=Entre la France et l'Algérie, le père de Rayan Cherki a pris position |url=https://observalgerie.com/2025/01/25/sports/france-algerie-pere-rayan-cherki-pris-position/ |access-date=22 September 2025 |website=observalgerie.com |language=fr-FR}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.liberte-algerie.com/sports/cherki-un-joyau-que-la-federation-doit-viser-314756|title=Cherki, un joyau que la fédération doit viser: Toute l'actualité sur liberte-algerie.com|website=Liberte Algerie|access-date=19 October 2019|archive-date=28 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128073635/https://www.liberte-algerie.com/sports/cherki-un-joyau-que-la-federation-doit-viser-314756|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Rayan Cherki (OL), une entreprise familiale façon Kylian Mbappé – Foot – L1 – OL|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/Rayan-cherki-ol-une-entreprise-familiale-facon-kylian-mbappe/1102643|access-date=29 January 2020|website=L'Équipe|language=fr}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Lyon===
Cherki is a product of the [[Olympique Lyonnais Reserves and Academy|youth academy of Lyon]], and is considered one of their best-ever prospects. He began playing with their reserve side in the [[Championnat National 1|Championnat National 2]] at the age of 15.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnews.fr/sport/2019-10-19/qui-est-rayan-cherki-le-grand-espoir-du-football-francais-817046|title=Qui est Rayan Cherki, le grand espoir du football français ?|website=cnews.fr|date=20 January 2020|language=fr}}</ref> On 7 July 2019, Cherki signed his first professional contract with [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon]] until 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ol.fr/Contents/Articles/2019/07/02/signature-rayan-cherki-signe-son-premier-contrat-pro|title=Rayan Cherki signs first professional contract with OL|website=OL.fr|publisher=Olympique Lyonnais|date=7 July 2019}}</ref> He made his professional debut in a 0–0 [[Ligue 1]] draw against [[Dijon FCO|Dijon]] on 19 October 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ca.soccerway.com/matches/2019/10/19/france/ligue-1/olympique-lyonnais/dijon-football-cote-dor/3030645/|title=Olympique Lyonnais vs. Dijon – 19 October 2019 – Soccerway|publisher=Soccerway}}</ref> After scoring four goals in the [[2019–20 UEFA Youth League]], he made his senior European debut on 27 November 2019 in a [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League group stage|Champions League group stage game]] against [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]], aged 16 years and 102 days,<ref>{{cite web |date=29 July 2020 |title=The UEFA Champions League's youngest players |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0253-0d042a009474-d3a14de143a9-1000--youngest-champions-league-players-moukoko-yamal-babayaro-c/ |publisher=UEFA}}</ref> in which he substituted [[Maxwel Cornet]] in the 74th minute of a 2–0 loss.<ref>{{cite web |date=27 November 2019 |title=Zenit v Lyon game report |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2027093--zenit-vs-lyon/ |publisher=UEFA}}</ref>

[[File:Rayan Cherki 2019.jpg|thumb|Cherki on his [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League group stage|UEFA Champions League]] debut game against [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] in 2019|left|300x300px]]

On 4 January 2020, Cherki scored his first senior goal as a substitute in a 7–0 win over [[Football Bourg-en-Bresse Péronnas 01|Bourg-en-Bresse]] in the [[2019–20 Coupe de France|Coupe de France]], becoming the youngest-ever player to score a senior goal for Lyon, aged 16 years and 140 days.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ol.fr/en/contents/articles/2020/01/05/after-bourg-ol-cdf-rayan-cherki-youngest-scorer-in-ol-history |title=After Bourg – OL (CDF) : Rayan Cherki, the youngest scorer in the history of OL |website=OL.fr |publisher=Olympique Lyonnais |date=5 January 2020 |accessdate=24 January 2020}}</ref> On 18 January, he was involved in all four of Lyon's goals in a 4–3 win over [[FC Nantes|Nantes]] in another Coupe de France match; he scored a brace, and assisted the other two goals.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ligue1.com/autresCompetitions/article/cherki-praised-as-teenage-sensation-stars-in-lyon-win.htm|title=Cherki praised as teenage sensation stars in Lyon win|website=ligue1.com|date=19 January 2020|accessdate=19 January 2020}}{{Dead link|date=February 2022 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On 19 August, Cherki was subbed on in a [[UEFA Champions League]] match against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]]. In doing so, he became the youngest-ever player to feature in a Champions League semi-final.<ref>{{Cite web|last=May|first=Sam|date=5 September 2020|title=Rayan Cherki: All you need to know about Lyon's 17-year-old wonderkid|url=https://thefootballfaithful.com/rayan-cherki-lyon-player-profile-transfer-news/|access-date=21 September 2020|website=The Football Faithful}}</ref> Lyon were knocked out of the competition in that match, losing 3–0 to the eventual winners.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Dawkes|first=Phil|date=19 August 2020|title=Bayern breeze past Lyon to set up PSG showdown|language=en-GB|work=BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53815521|access-date=21 September 2020}}</ref>

Cherki scored his first Ligue 1 goal in a 3–2 win over [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] on 2 May 2021. His goal secured the victory for Lyon in the final minutes of the match.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2 May 2021|title=Rayan Cherki late goal earns Lyon win at Monaco to keep Champions League qualification push alive|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/ligue-1/2020-2021/rayan-cherki-late-goal-earns-lyon-win-at-monaco-to-keep-champions-league-qualification-push-alive_sto8302008/story.shtml|access-date=3 May 2021|publisher=Eurosport}}</ref>

In September 2024, Cherki extended his stay with the club until 2027.<ref>{{Cite web |date=21 September 2024 |title=Rayan Cherki prolonge son contrat avec l'OL et postule pour le match face à l'OM |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Rayan-cherki-prolonge-son-contrat-avec-l-ol-et-postule-pour-le-match-face-a-l-om/1509165 |access-date=2025-03-29 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> The extension included an optional year, which would be automatically activated if he was still under contract with Lyon on 1 September 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |date=21 September 2024 |title=Football. OL: Rayan Cherki prolonge son contrat de deux ans |url=https://www.leprogres.fr/sport/2024/09/21/ol-rayan-cherki-prolonge-son-contrat-de-deux-ans |access-date=2025-03-29 |website=Le Progrès |language=FR-fr}}</ref> Following the contract extension, Cherki emerged as a standout player for Lyon, finishing as the league’s top assist provider with 11, and earning him a place in the [[Trophées UNFP du football|UNFP Team of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.footmercato.net/a9038956981218666999-trophees-unfp-2025-le-onze-type-de-la-saison-en-ligue-1|title=Trophées UNFP 2025 : le onze type de la saison en Ligue 1 !|publisher=Foot Mercato|date=11 May 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Rayan-cherki-leve-toute-ambiguite-et-prend-la-tete-du-classement-des-meilleurs-passeurs-a-la-derniere-journee/1562745|title=Rayan Cherki lève toute ambiguïté et prend la tête du classement des meilleurs passeurs à la dernière journée|publisher=L'Équipe|date=18 May 2025}}</ref> He was also given the inaugural Ligue 1 Dribbler of the Year award.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sofoot.com/breves/lyon-rayan-cherki-elu-meilleur-dribbleur-de-ligue-1-face-a-ousmane-dembele-et-desire-doue|title=Et le meilleur dribbleur de Ligue 1 est...|publisher=So Foot|date=15 May 2025}}</ref> In the [[2024–25 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]], Cherki delivered eight assists, making him the competition’s top assist provider and playing a key role in helping Lyon reach the quarter-finals. His performances were further recognized with the competition's Young Player of the Season award and a place in the Team of the Season, highlighting his development and growing influence at both domestic and European levels.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/olympique-lyonnais/ligue-europa-rayan-cherki-designe-meilleur-jeune-joueur-de-la-saison-2024-2025-5ee9c9da-3730-11f0-bf6c-240af7605eff|title=Ligue Europa. Rayan Cherki désigné meilleur jeune joueur de la saison 2024-2025|publisher=Ouest-France|date=11 May 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.olympique-et-lyonnais.com/ligue-europa-cherki-ol-nomme-meilleur-jeune-joueur-et-present-dans-le-onze-type,362628.html|title=Ligue Europa : Cherki (OL) nommé meilleur jeune joueur et présent dans le onze type|publisher=Olympique et Lyonnais|date=23 May 2025}}</ref>

===Manchester City===
On 10 June 2025, [[Premier League]] club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] announced the signing of Cherki on a five-year contract for a reported initial fee of €36.5m, a potential €6m in add-ons, and a 15% sell-on clause.<ref>{{cite web |date=10 June 2025 |title=City seal signing of Cherki |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/rayan-cherki-announcement-63885169 |access-date=10 June 2025 |publisher=[[Manchester City F.C.]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ol.fr/fr/actualites/merci-rayan-et-bonne-continuation|title=Merci Rayan et bonne continuation ! |date=10 June 2025 |access-date=11 June 2025 |publisher=Olympique Lyonnais |language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Collins |first=Ben |date=10 June 2025 |title=Lyon's Cherki completes 'dream' £30m Man City move |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cx2jzlxd9eeo |access-date=10 June 2025 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> On 22 June, he scored his first goal for the club in a 6–0 [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup|FIFA Club World Cup]] group stage victory against [[Al Ain FC|Al Ain]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/fifa-club-world-cup/man-city-v-al-ain-fifa-club-world-cup-match-report-63886230 |title=City cruise into Club World Cup knockouts with Al Ain win |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=23 June 2025 |access-date=23 June 2025}}</ref> On 14 August, after [[Jack Grealish]]'s departure on loan to [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], Cherki was given the [[Squad number (association football)|number 10 shirt]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/rayan-cherki-number-10-63890702 |title=Cherki to wear No.10 shirt |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=14 August 2025 |access-date=14 August 2025}}</ref> On 16 August, Cherki scored on his Premier League debut for City after coming on as a substitute for [[Erling Haaland]] in a 4–0 away victory over [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] in their season opener.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/wolves-manchester-city-202526-match-report-63890951 |title=Super City make blistering Premier League start at Wolves |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=16 August 2025 |access-date=16 August 2025}}</ref> On 29 October, Cherki registered a goal and an assist on his [[EFL Cup]] debut in a 3–1 away victory over [[EFL Championship]] side [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] in the [[2025–26 EFL Cup#Fourth round|fourth round]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/swansea-v-manchester-city-carabao-cup-round-4-match-report-63897361 |title=City into Carabao Cup quarter-finals |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=29 October 2025 |access-date=30 October 2025}}</ref> On 5 November, Cherki scored his first Champions League goal in a 4–1 home [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League league phase#Matchday 4|league phase]] victory over [[Bundesliga]] side [[Borussia Dortmund]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-v-borussia-dortmund-match-report-ucl-5-november-63897968 |title=Foden-inspired City ease past Dortmund |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=5 November 2025 |access-date=5 November 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Cherki is eligible to play for either France, Algeria, or Italy – the latter two due to his parents' origin.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lyon hotshot Cherki called up by France for Nations League |url=https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20250521-lyon-hotshot-cherki-called-up-by-france-for-nations-league |work=France 24 |date=21 May 2025 |language=en}}</ref> He played for the [[France national under-16 football team|France national under-16 team]] twice in 2018, both of which were [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly matches]] against [[Denmark national under-17 football team|Denmark]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fff.fr/equipes-de-france/tous-les-joueurs/fiche-joueur/2545493034-mathis-cherki|title=Joueur {{!}} Rayan Cherki|publisher=[[French Football Federation]]|language=fr|access-date=29 January 2020|archive-date=3 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803230038/https://www.fff.fr/equipes-de-france/tous-les-joueurs/fiche-joueur/2545493034-mathis-cherki|url-status=dead}}</ref>

In 2024, Cherki was named in [[France Olympic football team|France U23]]'s squad for the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|Olympic Games]] hosted in France.<ref>{{cite tweet |author=French Football Federation |author-link=French Football Federation |user=equipedefrance |number=1810268841097724078 |date=8 July 2024 |title=𝐿𝐼𝑆𝑇𝐸 𝑂𝐹𝐹𝐼𝐶𝐼𝐸𝐿𝐿𝐸 📋⚽️ Ils représenteront la France aux 𝑱𝒆𝒖𝒙 𝑶𝒍𝒚𝒎𝒑𝒊𝒒𝒖𝒆𝒔 de @Paris2024 🇫🇷🫡 #BleuCollectif |access-date=8 July 2024 }}</ref> He appeared in three games during the tournament, starting in the last group stage game against [[New Zealand Olympic football team|New Zealand]], and then appeared as a substitute in the semi-final game against [[Egypt Olympic football team|Egypt]], and then in the final against [[Spain Olympic football team|Spain]], as France won the silver medal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.olympique-et-lyonnais.com/ol-france-cherki-et-lepenant-des-jo-mitiges,336819.html|title=OL - France : Cherki et Lepenant, des JO mitigés|website=olympique-et-lyonnais.com|date=7 August 2024 |access-date=13 July 2025}}</ref> Being an Olympic medalist, Cherki was awarded the [[Knight of the National Order of Merit]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Rayan-cherki-et-alexandre-lacazette-ont-recu-leur-medaille-de-chevalier-de-l-ordre-national-du-merite-a-lyon/1561575|title=Rayan Cherki et Alexandre Lacazette ont reçu leur médaille de chevalier de l'ordre national du Mérite à Lyon|publisher=L'Équipe|access-date=13 July 2025}}</ref>

Cherki debuted for the [[France national football team|French senior squad]] on 5 June 2025, scoring and assisting in a 5–4 loss against [[Spain national football team|Spain]] in the [[2025 UEFA Nations League Finals|Nations League semi-finals]].<ref>{{Cite web|first=Oliver|last=Hopkins|title=Rayan Cherki is Europe's King of Chance Creation – It's Why Man City Want Him|url=https://theanalyst.com/articles/rayan-cherki-lyon-man-city-transfer-chance-creation-stats|website=The Analyst|date=6 June 2025|access-date=10 June 2025}}</ref> Three days later, on 9 June, he earned his first start in a 2–0 victory against [[Germany national football team|Germany]] in the same tournament.<ref>{{Cite web|first=Nukul|last=Jashoria|title='He needs to be at the heart of the game' – Rayan Cherki hailed as an example for France's other youngsters as Didier Deschamps reflects on Man City-bound star's strong start for national team|url=https://www.goal.com/en-in/lists/game-rayan-cherki-hailed-example-france-stars-didier-deschamps-reflects-man-city-national-team/bltf2cfab79fe8b11e8#csc8434a91c827c932|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=9 June 2025|access-date=10 June 2025}}</ref>

